# Fix Lang Project Rules

## System

- macOS Apple Silicon
- Electron

## Technical Stack

- Electron JS
- TypeScript
- React
- OpenAI API
- Tailwind CSS
- Vite
- Bun as package manager

## General Rules

- Always start response with `I’ve already read the rules\n`
- Always analyze the task before starting
  - Plan how to implement
  - Break down the task into smaller steps
  - Add task to `plan.md` as TODO list
- Always use `plan.md` to guide your work but not follow it very strictly
- Always analyze `src/main/index.ts`, `src/preload/index.ts`, `electron.vite.config.ts` before starting to know the code base structure
- Look inside `package.json` to know the dependencies before asking to install packages
- Mark the task in `plan.md` as complete when you finish it with a summary of the implementation and accessibility notes

## Coding Rules

- Use TypeScript for all code
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Prefer `type` over `interface`
- Follow SOLID principles, keep code simple and maintainable and easy to test
- Use descriptive variable names
- Prefer `const` over `function` for declarations
- Keep files below 200 lines of codes, split into smaller files if necessary
